<new>This is one of the most exciting things to come out of England, and it certainly lives up to its reputation. The tension when we have to find out whether or not Lembach is staying is amazing, and it keeps you on the edge of your seat. The upside is seeing the charming secretary, Sheila, and her unique fashion sense, which adds a touch of humor to the movie. This movie showcases several beautiful views of London, and it captures the essence of the city's charm. There is also a thrilling car chase that keeps the adrenaline pumping, and it adds a sense of urgency to the movie. There is also a watch that gets lost in the chaos, and the mystery of finding the watch is parallel to the thrill of a scavenger hunt. Add on a high-stakes shootout between the British police and the Dr. Rat, which leads to an epic showdown, plus the electrifying atmosphere of a villain's hideout, plus a cute cat and you have yourself... ummm... A British classic. The MST3K version is fantastic, and it's one of their best parodies to date.
